Ad Text:
12 + 6 + 6 month contract - ASAP Start
Baseline Security Clearance Preferred
Provide hands-on BA services across multiple projects

Our client, a Federal Government organisation responsible for executing economic & fiscal policy, market regulation & the delivery of the federal budget, require the services of multiple Senior Business Analyst(s).

Duties of the Senior Business Analyst

Understand business processes & determine business requirements for systems;
Provide hands-on services, across multiple projects at various stages of the development lifecycle including requirements analysis, design, testing & release;
Support the technical team on a range of tasks, including supporting project deliverables of new business requirements & enhancements to existing solutions;
Documentation & knowledge transfer to ensure sufficient business records are created;
Liaise between ICT staff & business areas to evaluate, analyse, & communicate systems requirements for project sprints.

Skills and experience required

Business modelling: Level 4 (SFIA) - experience in advanced modelling activities for significant change programmes and across multiple business functions;
Business process improvement: Level 5 (SFIA) - ability to manage the execution of business process improvements, analysing & designing business processes to identify alternative solutions to improve efficiency;
Requirements definition & management: Level 5 (SFIA) - ability to plan and scope requirements definition for complex initiatives;

 Desirable criteria

Data modelling and design: Level 4 (SFIA) - ability to plan data modelling & design activities;
Methods and tools: Level 4 (SFIA) - advise / support the adoption of methods & tools 
Stakeholder relationship management: Level 5 (SFIA) - a high degree of stakeholder liaison experience & communication skills;
User experience analysis: Level 4 (SFIA) - ability to develop user stories & elicit user experience requirements in complex situations. 

How to Apply 
To apply for this Senior Business Analyst contract opportunity, please get in touch with Daniel at Recruitment Hive by clicking the Quick Apply button. Alternatively you can reach Dan on (02) 6299 1006 to discuss further. 


Please note that applications close on Wednesday the 18th of March 2026 at 11am. Recruitment Hive welcome  late applications to be considered for future opportunities. 


Job ID: DE666822 | LH-05723
 

